summary: Mohammad Farooq from ITC called to report a complaint about a pack of ABC noodles that he bought from his supermarket in Tamil Nadu that appeared to be damaged and which may have fungus. The executive, Praveen, notes down his details, including his name, address, and phone number, as well as details of the product and the complaint. Farooq requests that the company look into the matter and provides his email as a means of contacting him. The call ends with an assurance that the matter will be looked into.
speaker_a_summary: Praveen, an ITC customer, is having trouble with a packet of Magic Spices PNoodles that he bought from 73A Supermarket in Palangudi. He is complaining that the packet is broken and there is fungus on it. He wants to know if he can get a refund. He lives in Aalangudi, and his PIN is 62301. He speaks Tamil and can be reached at GQ D gangla ganga.
speaker_b_summary: A customer is calling the supermarket 'Supermarked' to complain about the BC noodles they purchased, which was damaged and had fungus. They explain the issue in detail, mentioning that the packet was red and it was supposed to be yellow. They also express that the noodles have fungus and the spices have spread, and request a replacement or a refund. The customer provides their contact details and hopes for a resolution to the issue. The employee at Supermarked offers an apology and assures the customer that they will look into the matter.
